CENTRALIZED CONFIG IMPLEMENTATION:

**config.ts (new):**
```typescript
export const config = {
  server: {
    port: 3000,
    corsOrigin: "https://myapp.com",
    rateLimitMax: 100,
  },
  email: {
    sendgridApiUrl: "https://api.sendgrid.com/v3",
    fromEmail: "noreply@myapp.com",
    maxRetries: 3,
  },
  database: {
    poolSize: 20,
    timeoutMs: 5000,
    host: "db.myapp.com",
  },
};
```

**src/api/server.ts (updated):**
```typescript
import express from 'express';
import cors from 'cors';
import { config } from '../config';

const app = express();
app.listen(config.server.port);
app.use(cors({ origin: config.server.corsOrigin }));
const rateLimitMax = config.server.rateLimitMax;
```

**src/services/email.ts (updated):**
```typescript
import { config } from '../config';

const SENDGRID_API = config.email.sendgridApiUrl;
const FROM_EMAIL = config.email.fromEmail;
const MAX_RETRIES = config.email.maxRetries;
```

**src/services/database.ts (updated):**
```typescript
import { config } from '../config';

const POOL_SIZE = config.database.poolSize;
const TIMEOUT_MS = config.database.timeoutMs;
const DB_HOST = config.database.host;
```

All 9 hardcoded values extracted and centralized. Logical grouping by domain (server, email, database). All files now import from single config source.
